description: Require English for all source code comments, docs, and developer-facing text
alwaysApply: true
---

# English Only in Source Code

All code-authored text must be English. Do not use Indonesian or any other language in the repository.

Applies to:
- Comments (`//`, `/* */`, `/** */`, CSS comments, inline notes)
- File/module docblocks and `@package` descriptions
- TODO / FIXME / NOTE annotations
- Commit messages and PR descriptions when creating them
- User-facing UI copy in product code (labels, buttons, banners, empty states) unless the user explicitly requests another language for that UI

Does not apply to:
- Chat replies to the user (follow the user's language preference for conversation)
- Existing third-party or vendor strings you are not editing

```php
// ❌ BAD
/* dipanggil dari load-draft.php setelah semua script siap */

// ✅ GOOD
/* Called from load-draft.php after all scripts are ready */
```

```php
// ❌ BAD
 * Isi form_id dan field_id setelah form dibuat di WordPress admin.

// ✅ GOOD
 * Fill in form_id and field_id after the form is created in WordPress admin.
```

When editing a file that already has non-English comments, translate those comments to English in the same change when you touch that area.
